# Adding load balancer to use both servers and have redundancy.
Load balance setup is active-active setup to receive requests in load balanced rotation

#How a database Primary-Replica (Master-Slave) cluster works?
the slave get master's updates or copy(replicate) and can take over if Master fail or under maintenance.
After maintenance or fix the old master assumes slave role and have a copy of master's data and can take over ...

#What is the difference between the Primary node and the Replica node in regard to the application?
Primary node receives requests from client, while replicant nodes replicates the primary node
# SPOF single point of failure
is Load balancer, as currently client is routed to load balancer whose failure might translate into server down
